original: Bengtsson, Oskar Hugo, komminister, Liared, f. 9/10/10 i As, Hall. 1., av smedm. Oscar B. o. Anna Andersson. G. 38 m. folkskoll. Marta Andersson. Barn: Håkan f. 39, Anne-Marie 42, Sten 43. — Stud:ex. 30, teol. fil. ex. 31, teol’. kand. 35, präsitv. f. Skara st. 35. Komminister i Liared fr. 38. Ordf. i kyrkost., skolråd o. barnavmd.
translated: Bengtsson, Oskar Hugo, curate, Liared, born on October 9th, 1910 in As, Halland, the son of blacksmith Oscar B. and Anna Andersson. He married Marta Andersson in 1938, who had completed primary school education. They had three children: Håkan born in 1939, Anne-Marie born in 1942, and Sten born in 1943. Oskar graduated from high school in 1930, received a Bachelor of Arts in theology in 1931, completed his theology degree in 1935, and was ordained a priest for the Skara station in 1935. He became curate in Liared in 1938 and served as chairperson in the church council, school board, and child welfare committee.
